quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  9,75,Some de them et pledged Si DEUS showered nos His gratia nos est charitable lead righteous vita
  9,76,when He perfecit shower them His provisions they became stingy turned aversion
  9,77,Consequently He pestis them hypocrisy their hearts feria they meet Eum. Hoc est because they broke their promises DEUS because de their lying
  9,78,they non realize ut DEUS knows their secrets their conspiracies DEUS est Knower totus secrets
  9,79,Those criticize generous believers dedit too much ridicule poor believers dedit too parvus DEUS despises them! They incurred painful retribution
  9,80,Vos ask forgiveness them non ask forgiveness them! - Et si vos ask forgiveness them 70 temporis - DEUS testimentum NON forgive them! Hoc est they disbelieve DEUS His messenger. DEUS NON guide wicked people
  9,81,sedentary rejoiced their staying messenger DEUS hated strive their moneta their vita in causa DEUS! They dictus not mobilize in hoc heat Dictus fire Hell est much hotter they unus comprehend
  9,82,"Let them laugh ut parvus, cry ut lot! Hoc est requital sins they earned"
  9,83,Deus returns vos situation ubi they ask tuus disponsationis mobilize vos vos dictus Vos perfecit nunquam again mobilize me nor testimentum vos ever fight me any enemy Vos chosen est cum sedentary in the 1 locus. Ergo vos stay cum the sedentary
  9,84,Vos non observe funeral prayer any de them when he abiit nor shall vos stand his grave They disbelieved DEUS His messenger abiit dictus wickedness
  9,85,Non impressed their moneta their infans; DEUS causa these est stirps misery them in hoc saeculum their anima obiit disbelievers
  9,86,When sura revealed dictus Believe in DEUS strive His messenger et strong among them dictus stay behind
  9,87,They chose est cum the sedentary. Consequently their hearts sigillum sic they non comprehend
  9,88,Prout pro messenger those believed eum they eagerly strive their moneta their vita. These deserved totus bonus things; they est winners
  9,89,DEUS prepared them gardens flowing streams wherein they abide forever Hoc est major triumph
  9,90,Arabs factus up excuses advenit vos seeking disponsationis stay behind Hoc est indicative de their rejection DEUS His messenger - they stay behind Indeed those disbelieve them incurred painful retribution
  9,91,Non to blamed est those est infirmus male non invenit anything offer long prout they remain devoted to DEUS His messenger! righteous among them non blamed DEUS est Forgiver Merciful
  9,92,Alias excused est those advenit vos wishing included vos vos tell them ego non habet anything carry vos They tunc turn tears their eyes genuinely saddened they non afford contribute